features: If you have a pile of flash drives, each time you need one you have to take a lot of time to find where they are and which one if for what, then you need one flash drive organizer case. With 20 slots, this usb bag helps you to keep the desktop clean and work more effecient. The usb case comes with label sheet, which you can use to identify each one of your memory stick.
Made of high quality neoprene, the USB drive holder is resilient, dustproof, anti-static and anti-scratch. Thick and sturdy enough to protect your gadgets inside from shocking and other damage.
USB flash drive storage case got the nice and sturdy zipper, seams are snug and secure. The thumb drive case can hold your pen drives without any worry.
The usb drive case got 20 standard size slots for ten jump drives. Double storage space by contrast with the old version. Easy to close with all 20 USB drives inside.
JBOS provides a 1 years warranty for all our customers. If you want to customize usb flash drives with your logo, visit JBOS Sotre to start.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Durable and convenient.
reviews.reviewText: This is a durable and convenient usb drive case. It is as described and pictured. The material quality is smooth and sleek. I love the zipper closure and elastic slots. This keeps everything organized in one place. The price point is good for this well-made case. I would recommend for any home, office, commercial, personal or professional use. This is nice to have for many different project/organization ideas.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works OK but is a little difficult to insert USB Flash Drive Stick into some of the slots...
reviews.reviewText: I was excited when I saw this because I have a bunch of "USB thumb drives" that lived in a coffee cup on my desk. Invariably I wouldn't have THE one that I needed when I was away from my desk, so I anticipated this would be the perfect solution! I could store ALL of my "USB thumb drives" in it and just grab them all at once in the case and never be without the "right" one!AND it would be the perfect solution - IF you plan on using it as it was designed to be used - with "USB thumb drives" that make use of the 20 small stickers included for labeling the drives.Unfortunately, I have already attached some plastic key ring tags with labels on them so I know what's on the drive. They take up extra spaces and as a result of the size of the key ring tags, I cannot zip the case shut.So I'm giving it 4 starts based on my particular use case. AND I'm betting you can have a 5-star experience with this IF you use it as intended!Oh, and as an unannounced bonus, the plastic zip-lock bag it comes in is very sturdy and has a "zipper" that closes it as well. So you actually end up getting "a second bag" that can be very useful for free! (See the last image on the Amazon product page as it shows the USB storage case inside the plastic zip-lock bag.)

reviews.reviewText: I wanted to have a safe place to store all of our family photos in one spot. This flash drive holder is perfect for holding a ton of different drives, and folds up neatly into a case. We are putting it in our fireproof safe to keep all our important items in one location.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works best for thinner or smaller flash drives
reviews.reviewText: I tested this flash drive case with several different style flash drives, some were thin and small, others were bulky in size and shape. The elastic holders on the outside of the case fit larger flash drives while you can still fit those on the inner sections, it is quite challenging to fit them in. When you fill the case, it becomes bulky but the fabric itself stretches easy to close the case. Along with the case, you receive small labels to help with your organization needs. You can label your drives before you put them in the case.
